Adrian Pillow <Apillow(-at-)manh.com> wrote:
> The IRS conversion is such a variable thing it is hard to
> say what is right
> or wrong depending on the path you want to go down.
>=20
> The only Thing components I know of that are used in a
> regular swap is the
> IRS tranny and/or inner flanged for the CVs.  I have never
> seen Thing CVs
> used.  Normally people use the baywindow CVs 28 degree
> working angle or the
> T4 CVs with a 32 degree working angle (expensive like $75
> each).
>=20
> Check out Bus Boys for details on what seems to be the route
> you are going.
> Volksworld did a DIY article on this a while ago as well.
>=20
> From my research you will need to buy modified axles,
> control arm mounts
> (clamp on or welded), and maybe spring plates.
>=20
> Old Speed has a stock height kit that uses Beetle stuff...=20
> Which means you
> can put early 944 rear brakes on it :)   Or T3 brakes.
>=20
> The shop talk forum usually has loads of custom information
> if you want to
> check it out.
>=20
